rules: Rule1: Provided that region1 has funding for conference1, then conference1 is successful.
Rule2: Either region1 has funding for conference1 or organization1 has funding for conference1.
Rule3: If paper1 needs copyright, then whenever conference1 publishes proceedings, proceedings1 has an ISBN.
Rule4: Paper1 needs copyright or paper1 has Creative Commons.
Rule5: Supposing that paper1 is submitted by author1, then if paper1 has Creative Commons, provided that conference1 publishes proceedings, proceedings1 has an ISBN.
Rule6: Either paper1 is submitted by author1 or paper1 is coauthored by author2.
Rule7: Assuming paper1 is coauthored by author2, then if paper1 has Creative Commons, whenever conference1 publishes proceedings, proceedings1 has an ISBN.
Rule8: If conference1 has a keynote, then it has an international keynote.
Rule9: If conference1 has a workshop, then it has a workshop approved.
Rule10: Given that conference1 has a workshop scheduled, then it has a local keynote.
Rule11: Under the condition that conference1 has an industry sponsor, then it has an exhibition.
Rule12: Either conference1 has an industry sponsor or it has an academic sponsor.
Rule13: If conference1 has an exhibition pending, then it has an exhibition approved.
Rule14: Under the condition that conference1 has a deadline extended, then it does not have a venue changed.
Rule15: If conference1 has reviewing started, then it has submission closed.
Rule16: Assuming conference1 has a program chair assigned, then if it has reviews completed, it has reviewing started.
Rule17: Either conference1 has a program chair assigned or it has a program committee formed.
Rule18: Conference1 has a proceedings publisher or, if it has a program committee formed, then provided that it has reviews completed, it has reviewing started.
Rule19: Either conference1 requires membership or, if it is not the case that having organization1 funding implies conference success, then it uses venue1.
Rule20: If conference1 is an open conference, then it does not require membership.
Rule21: Provided that conference1 is a free conference, then it does not require membership.
Rule22: Supposing conference1 has a scholarship, then if it is not the case that it is open or free, it is a paid conference.
Rule23: Either conference1 has a scholarship or it has a waiver.
Rule24: Conference1 accepts paper1 or, if it is not the case that having organization1 funding implies conference success, then it uses venue1.
Rule25: Provided that conference1 has a scholarship approved, then it has a scholarship granted.
Rule26: Either conference1 has a scholarship approved or it has a scholarship pending.
Rule27: Assuming conference1 has a scholarship pending, then if it has a waiver, under the condition that it is not open or free, it is a paid conference.
Rule28: If conference1 has a scholarship granted, then whenever it has a waiver, provided that it is not open or free, it is a paid conference.
Rule29: Under the condition that conference1 has a social event, then if it has a workshop approved, it has a workshop scheduled.
Rule30: Provided that conference1 has a reception scheduled, then it has a banquet scheduled.
Rule31: If conference1 is student organized, then it has a game night.
Rule32: Conference1 is student organized or it is faculty organized.
Rule33: Supposing conference1 requires registration, then it does not accept paper1.
Rule34: Given that conference1 is faculty organized, then if it is not the case that having a workshop implies it is scheduled, it has a workshop cancelled.
Rule35: Provided that conference1 has an industry partner, then it has a corporate partner.
Rule36: Either conference1 has an industry partner or it has a university partner.
Rule37: If conference1 has a university partner, then whenever it has an academic sponsor, it is successful.
Rule38: Under the condition that conference1 has a partnership confirmed, then if it has an academic sponsor, it is successful.
Rule39: If conference1 has a publication, then provided that it is not the case that having a corporate partner implies partnership confirmed, it does not have a partnership pending.
Rule40: Assuming conference1 has a journal special issue, then if it is not the case that having a corporate partner implies partnership confirmed, it does not have a partnership pending.
Rule41: Provided that conference1 has proceedings published, then it has a publication.
Rule42: If conference1 has a journal published, then it has a journal special issue.
Rule43: Provided that it is not the case that having a keynote implies no international keynote, then it has a workshop.
Rule44: If it is not the case that having a workshop implies it is scheduled, then it does not have a workshop cancelled.
Rule45: Under the condition that it is not the case that having a workshop approved implies it is scheduled, then it has a workshop rejected.
Rule46: Provided that it is not the case that having organization1 funding implies conference success, then it has a venue changed.
Rule47: Supposing it is not the case that having organization1 funding implies conference success, then it does not use venue1.
Rule48: Provided that it is not the case that having an academic sponsor implies conference success, then it has an exhibition pending.
Rule49: Under the condition that it is not the case that having a deadline implies it is extended, then it has reviews completed.
Rule50: If it is not the case that having a corporate partner implies partnership confirmed, then it has a partnership pending.
Rule51: Under the condition that it is not the case that conference1 has proceedings published or a journal published, then it has no publication.
Rule52: Provided that it is not the case that not requiring registration implies early registration, then it has late registration.
Rule53: If it is not the case that not requiring registration implies early registration, then it does not have late registration.
Rule54: Provided that conference1 does not have a social event, then it has a reception scheduled.
Rule55: Under the condition that conference1 does not have a social event, then it does not have a banquet scheduled.
Rule56: Provided that conference1 does not require registration, then it does not have early registration.
Rule57: Supposing conference1 is not successful, then it has a keynote.
Rule58: If conference1 is not successful, then it publishes proceedings.
